From c3ad1467f1a711a0cefcd63bae8892020a1c10d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 21:44:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] fix: FeedbackOverview no longer crashes on missing review
 arrays
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Defensive defaults for reviewsGiven/reviewsReceived/returnsSubmitted —
without them the guide modal white-screened for students whenever the
guide data was missing one of the arrays. Modernized the test mocks to
the current field names (feedbackGiven/feedbackReceived were renamed
long ago, so the suite was testing a crash instead of behavior) and
removed test cases for the deleted students-grade-reviews feature.
