From 5c4d287f10039aa4c1f95934efa59d1f92087ce1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 21:45:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] feat(returns): real URL validation, normalization, and a
 success state

- projectUrl/liveVersion are validated as actual URLs server-side
  (pictureUrl too when present); a typo'd link otherwise lands on the
  CLASSMATE assigned to review the return
- the form normalizes bare domains to https:// before submitting and
  reflects it back into the fields
- submitting no longer hard-redirects to /guides: the student gets a
  success panel explaining the peer-review contract (queue, the reviews
  they owe, where the result appears) and router.refresh() updates the
  guide status behind the modal
- shared LoadingSpinner/EmptyState/ErrorState components introduced
  (used app-wide in a follow-up commit)
